Comments: Casing originally placed at 6 m but was a boulder so recassed down to 12m. Appears to be bedrock from 11.5 m onwards.

Massive to weakly foliated unit with weak fuchsite alteration. Irregular dark grey domains (carb altn). Irregular stockwork of quartz carb veins, and smokey quartz veins. Trace to weak disseminated and blebby pyrite.

Grey coloured dominantly massive, fine-grained and graunular, non-foliated unit with very faint fuchsite alteration. Irregular facture pattern accentuated by darker grey alteration; possible relict jointing texture. Weak to sparse disseminated pyrite and chalcopyrite. Could be mafic or ultramafic unit (may be a dyke?)

Massive grey unit with a granular texture and grey carbonate altn accentuated along an irregular fracture pattern. Chlorite (+- talc) alteration along foliation planes. Irregular and blobby quartz-carb veins throughout. Weak to sparse disseminated pyrite.

Massive greyish-brown unit with an aphanitic texture and very small needles of rutile (<1mm). Pervasive carbonate alteration +- sericite/chlorite. Irregular patchy strong albite alteration. Trace disseminated pyrite.

Massive grey to green unit with an aphanitic to granular texture and an apparent breccia texture accentuated by an irregular stockwork of quartz-carb veins/altn. Weak fuchsite alteration. Oxidation on fracture surfaces (goethite/limonite) throughout but particularly concentrated at ~ 36m. Weak to moderate disseminated pyrite an cpy. Gradational to lower albitic altered unit.

Banded unit with light grey albite-carbonate alteration bands and chlorite altered bands. Strongly foliated and  folded bands and contorted domains. Irregular Qtz-Carb vein network. Weak to trace disseminated pyrite. 
 @49.15-49.35m: Very intense foliation and black chloritic/sulfidic bands, could be a fault or a strongly sheared sedimentary sequence.

Grey to tan unit with a stongly albite-quartz alteration and thin irregular wisps of chlorite alteration along foliation planes. Possible varioles (< 5 mm elongate quartz nodules). Moderate, very fine-grained disseminated pyrite.

Grey to green ultramafic with dark grey domains of quartz-carbonate and weaker fuchsite alteration. Apparent breccia texture has a strong orange oxidation around fragment margins. Irregular quartz-carb domains and vein network cross-cut by smokey quartz veins. Moderate to strong disseminated pyrite and chalcopyrite.

Strongly foliated and banded ultramafic with thin dark (black) quartz veins (<3mm) parallel to foliation. Ultramafic domains have strong fuchsite alteration and a delicate fracture pattern that could be spinifex. Deformed milky quartz-carb veins crosscut by smokey quartz veins that host visible gold. Gold also observed rarely along the foliation planes. Abundant disseminated pyrite and chalcopyrite throughout.

Highly siliceous, quartz-flooded breccia with a fault at the top contact.  Breccia texture defined by 60% angular siliceous altered fragments in a very fine grained siliceous matrix. Interpreted as a siliceous altered tectonic breccia.

Dark grey to black massive unit with a strong siliceous alteration and chlorite-graphite-sulfides along foliation and fracture planes. Weak minor fuchsite altereation locally. Foliation is steep and wavy. Rutile flecks present and possible relict varioles and perlitic fragments from 68-75m. Moderate to strong disseminated pyrite, chalcopyrite and possible arsenopyrite.
Stope 08: Void encountered at 78.38m, pushed HQ rods through to 93m into the rock on the other side.Reduced to NQ and started coring again at 89.2m.

Brown to grey, granular ultramafic with carbonate-chlorite-sericite alteration. Massive to weakly foliated. Minor to no quartz-carb veins. Moderate disseminated pyrite throughout. Gradational lower contact to fuchsite and quartz-carbonate alteration.

Bright emerald green, strongly quartz-carbonate-fuchsite altered ultramafic with irregular white quartz-carbonate veins throughout. Weak to moderate disseminated sulfides and visible gold in quartz veins at 117.5 and 121m.

Bright emerald green, strongly quartz-carbonate-fuchsite altered ultramafic with irregular white quartz-carbonate veins/domains throughout. Abundant orange "carbonate/sphene" crystals throughout.Gradational to lower brown unit. Moderate disseminated pyrite.

Brown to greenish, massive um unit with a granular texture. Moderate to strong quartz-carb replacement and weak fuchsite alteration. Gradational to stronger fuchsite altered domains. Sparse white quartz carb veins. Weak disseminated pyrite throughout.
Green-grey um with strong quartz-carbonate alteration and weak fuchsite plus trace chlorite altn. Gradational to upper brown UM unit. Spare quartz-carb veins and minor disseminated pyrite.
Abundant disseminated pyrite in a strongly albite altered dyke with sharp margins. Thin grey quartz veins, minor < 5mm wide, carbonate veins.

Bright emerald green ragged um domains and grey quartz-carb replaced domains. Fuchsite intensity is variable. Tan, silicified albite dyke from 159.35-159.65m. Abundant disseminated orange mineral. Disseminated pyrite along dark wispy bands defining foliation.
Dark brown ragged fragments (or apparent fragments) of um (or possibly mafic) with grey quartz-carbonate "infill". Trace fuchsite. Disseminated pyrite. Planar quartz-carb veins (non-deformed).

Green to grey um with ragged grey quartz-carbonate alteration separating fragments with foliation defined fuchsite alteration. Minor wispy grey stringer veins and planar irregular and discontinous to non-deformed milky white quartz-carb veins. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Upper contact is marked by a fault zone to 168m; followed by a breccia texture to the end of the interval. May be a zone of mixed lithology. Moderate to strong carbonate altn and ragged brown and locally fuchsite altered fragments. Minnor thin (<0.5cm) wide quartz veins.Trace disseminated pyrite.

Mixed interval of ultramafic and possible mafic dykes.Mafic dykes are tan coloured, have an internal breccia texture and have brecciated margins Alteration ranges in the ultramafic from dominantly brown to green fuchsite domains. Weak to moderate disseminated sulfides.
Green, weakly fuchsite altered ragged and wispy ultramafic lenses with a white quartz-carbonate infill. Moderate disseminated pyrite throughout and irregular, discontinuous white quartz-carb veins.

UM with alternating massive and quartz-carbonate banded domains. Moderate to strong carbonate altn with weak sericite and chlorite. Disseminated pyrite. Alteration banding is transitional to quartz-carbonate veins. Veining and banding has a similar orientation.

Zone of mixed ultramafic and sandstone to mudstone. Possible ultramafic domains and sediment domains.Ultramafic domains may be a primary breccia or mixed domains. Anastomosing carbonate domains and sericite-chlorite wispy lenses. Weak fuchsite alteration. Disseminated pyrite.

Gradational to upper ultramafic unit; thick to thin graded beds of apparent pebble to granule breccia - sandstone - to mudstone grain size variation. Beds grading downhole.Weak pervasive sericite-chlorite altn with local fuchsite alteration. Weak disseminated pyrite and sparse, thin and planar quartz-carb veins.

Alternating beds of dark grey-black mudstone and light grey sandstone. Black interbeds are weakly graphitic. Beds are contorted and folded. Clay gouge-filled discrete faults @ 239.75 (25cm) and @242.48 (25cm). Weak to moderate sericite-chlorite alteration. Trace disseminated pyrite.
Cased to 12 m, intersected BR at 11.35

Faulted, quartz – carbonate  - chlorite -sericite altered rock. Grey, semi-intact core, texture destroyed by qtz-carb-chl-ser flooding. Rubble < 10cm, Common fault gouge up to 3 cm along planes~30° to core axis. Local healed fault breccias.Trace pyrite.

Moderate foliation ~40°TCA defined by alternating quartz-carb bands with dark grey selvages, and fuchsite bands. Grey to dark green. Weak to moderate qtz-carb-fuchsite alteration. Common disseminated sulphides, Py and lesser Cpy approximately 5% total. Rare <1/m milky quartz veins <2cm thick cross cut foliation. Decreasing fuchsite 30 to 36 m

Mafic or Ultramafic. Light grey to locally brownish, local brecciation and healed fault fabric shallow TCA. Moderate quartz - carbonate flooding obscures texture. 	Sharp faulted upper contact at ~40° TCA. 	Weak to moderate disseminated pyrite.

Mafic or Ultramafic. Light grey to locally brown, massive equigranular texture. 	Weak patchy quartz carbonate ± chlorite alteration. Weak to trace disseminated pyrite. Discontinuous milky to smoky quartz veins and veinlets, typically shallow TCA

Ultramafic (UM). Gradual increase in fuchsite, associated with weak carbonate alteration. Grey to greenish, local patchy brown carbonate.Discrete fracture/faults, ~20° TCA, with FeOx coatings. Discrete shear zone 60.85 to 61, ~25° TCA. Weak to trace pyrite
Discrete Quartz-Carbonate vein ~20° TCA. Strong carbonate alteration at selvages. Trace pyrite

Ultramafic (UM). Dark grey to green. Weak pervasive quartz-carb fuchsite ±chlorite flooding. Abundant thin, dark grey wispy smoky quartz ‘veins’ and less common chunky milky quartz-carbonate veins. Weak disseminated pyrite, local thin pyrite wisps and rare sulphide aggregates
Quartz Vein, 	Top contact ~20°TCA. Dark grey-black massive quartz ±carbonate vein. Local inclusions of Qtz-flooded, fuchsite altered wall rock <20cm contain trace sulphides (Py).

Ultramafic (UM). Dark grey to green. Weak pervasive quartz-carb fuchsite ±chlorite flooding. Moderate foliation subparallel TCA. Abundant thin, dark grey wispy smoky quartz ‘veins’ and less common chunky milky quartz-carbonate veins. Thicker <3cm massive smoky quartz veins run sub-parallel TCA locally. Weak to moderate disseminated/blebby to subhedral pyrite (~5% locally), local thin pyrite stringers.

Silicified Ultramafic(?)/Healed Fault Breccia (UM, FAULT). Massive to brecciated intensely silicified dark grey to black rock. Local relict texture preserved; elongate flattened banding evident in breccias clasts/wall rock fragments.Common massive quartz veins subparallel TCA. Intense proliferance of thin dark quartz ‘stringers’. Intense pervasive quartz, patchy intense albite alteration, and fracture controlled chlorite alteration. Abundant disseminated to blebby pyrite up to ~7% locally. Possible trace arsenopyrite? Darkness of quartz stringers may be associated with very fine grained sulphide but not easily visible.

Massive multistage quartz vein. Contacts ~5-10° TCA; essentially drilling directly down dip. Relict wall rock textures locally preserved but totally silicified. Fracture controlled chlorite and graphite alteration towards lower contact. Trace pyrite

Strained, intensely foliated (10-20° TCA) ultramafic rock. Foliation defined by alterating bands of calcite/carbonate (strong reaction to dilute HCl. Abundant disseminated pyrite, ~2-3%, possible trace arsenopyrite. Weak local trace fuchsite. **135 to 137 brass smears from drill bit on core

Grey-blue, fine – grained, massive dyke. Sharp upper contact ~30° TCA, sub parallel to foliation. Weak to moderate foliation. Common quartz and calcite veins, 30 to 70° TCA, up to 12 cm thick. Moderate to strong chlorite –calcite alteration. Abundant disseminated pyrite, up to 5% locally.

Gradational (?) contact into massive green-grey rock with fragmental-looking, black, fine grained inclusions (sedimentary?) that appear to have been strained to brittle fracture. Calcite±pyrite veins favor these fractures but do not totally terminate at fragment boundaries. Common calcite±sulphide veins. Moderate vein envelope calcite alteration. Fine grained disseminated and euhedral pyrite, common vein hosted pyrite total ~5%. pXRF shots inconclusive to UM/M composition, local As to ~200 ppm

Mixed UM/M. Strained grey-white rock, strong banding (~5°TCA) defined by calcite-carbonate and lesser quartz. Strong chlorite-carbonate alteration, strong reaction to dilute HCl in wall rock and veins.
	pXRF shots inconclusive to UM/M composition. Locally faulted, sheared along core axis. Clay and chlorite coat surfaces. Nearly1 m core loss ~201 m. Disseminated pyrite favors foliation planes, up to 2%

Dark grey thickly bedded mafic sandstone with intercalated mudstone laminations. 	Bedded ~60° TCA. 	Strong chlorite-calcite alteration, intense reaction to HCl. 	Abundant wispy calcite stringers. 	Common disseminated subhedral to euhedral pyrite, up to 1%.
Cased to 9m

Grey banded mudstone to sandstone facies. 	Contorted bedding with sericite alteration developed strongly along foliation planes. 	Fault zone with quartz-carbonate boudins from 16.59 to 20.65m. Diffusely graded and bedded from 20.65 to 23.73m. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Grey-greenish unit with moderate and planar foliation. Stretched fragments of quartz-carbonate. Pervasive quartz-carbonate alteration with foliation parallel sericite-chlorite alteration. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Bright to light emerald green, fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic with domains of quartz-carbonate vein stockwork / bands throughout. Ultramafic fragments are ragged and boudinaged. 	Moderate to strong (0.5 to 2%) disseminated pyrite; strongest along fuchsite altered septa. Quartz-carbonate (brownish) flooded/vein zone from 33 to 34.65m. Gradational lower alteration contact.

Grey-brown massive ultramafic. 	Pervasive carbonate-quartz + weak chlorite amd weak sericite alteration. Trace fuchsite alteration along vein quartz-carbonate stockwork vein envelopes. 	Moderate disseminated pyrite. 	Gradational lower alteration contact.

Dark blue-grey chlorite-talc carbonate altered ultramafic. 	Breccia texture from 79.35 to ~87.00 defined by white carbonate-talc infill and boudinaged ultramafic fragments. Spinifex texture at 92.84m. Trace to moderate disseminated pyrite. Gradational lower alteration contact.
Grey brown carbonate-chlorite altered ultramafic, weak sericite. 	Irregular bands of quartz-carbonate (5-30%). Weak disseminated pyrite (~0.5%). 	Gradational lower alteration contact.

Bright emerald green fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic; gradational upper alteration contact. Bands/stockwork of white quartz-carbonate veins, up to 60% of the rock. Intense "flood" of quartz +- tourmaline vein/breccia infill from 116.73-117.50m. Weak to moderate disseminated pyrite.
Variably altered ultramafic fragments that range in size from 80cm to 5cm (fuchsite-quartz-carbonate, talc-chlorite-carbonate, tourmaline-quartz-carbonate vein breccia); sampled

Grey-emerald green fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic with a moderate foliation and mottled breccia texture. 5% white quartz-carbonate veins with diffuse margins, 50degTCA. 	Bright orange oxidation on fracture surfaces and throughout.

Emerald green fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic with 	15-20% quartz-carbonate vein stockwork, irregular diffuse infill and thin wispy irregular grey quartz-carbonate stringer veins. Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).
Albite-quartz-altered dykes with a sharp upper contact. Strong pervasive albite-quartz alteration. Strong disseminated pyrite (arsenian – silvery). Grades into broken friable rock.

Ultramafic; fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered fragments that range from 1cm to 20cm; often fragments have sharp margins with albitite dykes. 	Albitie dyke fragments; strong pervasive albite-quartz alteration and strong disseminated pyrite. 	Subangular to angular fragments. 	Poor recovery through this zone and the drill shift logs report hours of reaming and washing of sand out of the hole.

Tan to greyish, aphanitic, albitite dyke. Strong pervasive quartz-albite alteration. 	Strong (2-5%) disseminated and stringer vein pyrite and arsenopyrite. Planar white quartz-carbonate veins with diffuse margins. Sharp planar lower margin.

Greenish grey ultramafic unit with pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate (+- chlorite +- sericite) alteration and a medium to fine-grained granular texture. 	Irregular white quartz-carbonate veins with diffuse margins. Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).
Tan aphanitic, albitite dyke. Strong pervasive albite-quartz alteration and stockwork of thin greyish quartz-carbonate veins. Brassy disseminated pyrite (1-2%). Sharp, irregular margins.

Greenish grey ultramafic unit with pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration and a medium to fine-grained granular texture. 	Irregular white quartz-carbonate veins with diffuse margins, often greyish; cross-cut by irregular grey quartz-carbonate veins. 	Albitite dyke/boudins locally present; < 20cm wide. Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).

Polylithic angular rubble up to 1.5m diameter boulders; a total of 3.5 m of cored boulders, 1.3m of angular gravel, 5.38m void. Quartz vein fragment from 201.9-203m with significant VG throughout. 10 cm wide vein in a fragment at 203.8 with VG.

Greenish-grey homogeneous massive ultramafic unit with a fine- to medium-grained granular texture.	Pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration; weak sericite +- chlorite. 	5-10% irregular networks of quartz-carbonate veins; smokey grey  margins on veins. 	Weak to moderate disseminated pyrite.

Dark grey black aphanitic rocks with a  moderately well-developed monomitic breccia texture. Strong pervasive quartz-carbonate alteration +- albite. 	Irregular brecciated smokey grey quartz veins throughout. 	Strong pervasive disseminated pyrite and black sulfides (up to 20%). Very broken with several zones of core loss; angular friable rocks. Upper contact is a breccia; quartz-infill and angular veined fragments; interpretation = fault breccia.
Dark green-black, strongly foliated ultramafic. 	Strong pervasive talc-chlorite-carbonate alteration. 	Foliation ~ 60°TCA. 	Trace pyrite.

Variably altered banded to massive moderately foliated ultramafic with boudinaged albitic dykes. 	Alteration grades from moderate brown chlorite-carbonate (16.04 to 23 m) to weak fuchsite-quartz-carbonate (23 to 33.38 m). Patchy albite alteration occurs throughout. 	Quartz- carbonate replacement ~15%. 	Trace pyrite throughout. Stronger concentrations and trace chalcopyrite±tennantite occur in and around albitic altered zones. Oxidised fracture planes at 27 and 30 m blocks indicate open space. Approximately 3m core loss between 27 and 33 m.

Light grey to white phaneritic dyke with margins oriented ~45° (upper) and 70° (lower). 	Intense albite alteration. 	Pyrite occurs in a crackle-breccia-like sulphide vein stockwork and as fine disseminations. Trace black sulphide (possible tennantite) up to 8% total.
Chlorite-carbonate altered ultramafic cut by two short albitic dykes (35.26 - 35.4 m and 35.7 – 36 m). 	Dykes are light grey-pink and contain abundant disseminated pyrite and magnetite.

Grey green to emerald green ultramafic rocks with boudinaged albitic vein fragments and local apparently intact dykes. 	Alteration grades from strong chlorite-carbonate with minor talc to 41m to strong fuchsite quartz-carbonate. Rock becomes deeper emerald green with depth. Patchy albite alteration is present throughout. 	Quartz-carbonate replacement is ~25%. 	Trace to 1% disseminated pyrite, concentrated in albitic zones.

Strongly but patchily chlorite-carbonate (brown carbonate) altered, with variable amounts of talc. 	Local pyrite-mineralized boudinaged albite dyke fragment 67.4 m to 67.52 m. 	Weak disseminated pyrite throughout, local trace chalcopyrite.
Common orange prismatic mineral (rutile or carbonate?)

Broken blocky core, poor recovery. 	Interpreted as partially healed fault zone. 	Soft rubbly sections of strongly chlorite-sericite±talc altered rock in between semi competent hard zones of quartz-albitized breccia.	 Breccia sections contain up to 5% pyrite. 	Fabric oriented ~ 50° TCA. Strongly magnetic.

Dark emerald green, strongly fuchsite-altered (up to 35% quartz-carbonate replacement) ultramafic.	 Core is strongly silicified, and only weakly to moderately foliated. 	Quartz-carb flooding/veins with dark green to black septa containing pyrite and dark silver-black sulphides. Tennantite is present locally. Total sulphides ~3%.

Grey green, patchy quartz-chlorite-carbonate±weak fuchsite altered ultramafic. 	Moderate foliation ~ 70°TCA defined by quartz carbonate veins. 	Quartz-carbonate replacement ~15%, locally very strongly silicified. 	Lower contact defined by ~1m fault breccia oriented ~45° TCA. 	Trace pyrite throughout.
Strongly foliated, strongly talc-chlorite altered dark green ultramafic rocks. 	Common local faulting/shearing. 	Foliation ~ 40° TCA. 	Trace pyrite.

Intensely silicified grey-to bright green quartz-fuchsite altered ultramafic.	Texture is mottled with pervasive clear to grey quartz flooding, and locally banded with alternating rock/quartz-carbonate veins. 	Banding/foliation at ~50° TCA. 	Strongly disseminated pyrite up to 10%  over <30cm local intervals, common traces of chalcopyrite and tennantite. Total overall sulphides ~5%.

Variably brown-carbonate±fuchsite altered ultramafic rock. 	Drillers reported hitting sandy stope fill ~170 m. 	Strong oxidation of fracture planes, poor recovery (7 m loss over logged interval) and very common mis-latching of core ends. 	Common rubble.

Massive, black to dark grey mafic, possible diabase dyke intervals within but cannot distinguish contacts. Patchy weak albite alteration, pervasive calcite-chlorite alteration. 	Weakly foliated approximately 45° TCA. 	Strongly disseminated but patchy pyrite up to 3% overall.

Pale green-grey, strongly chlorite-calcite-sericite±patchy weak fuchsite altered ultramafic. Strongly foliated ~45° TCA.

Strongly foliated 45-50° TCA. 	Patchy euhedral pyrite. Local shearing/faulting. 	Not Sampled.

Strongly foliated 45-50° TCA. 	Patchy euhedral pyrite. Local shearing/faulting. 	Not Sampled.
Cased to 9m. 	Polylithic angular rubble from 8.60-9.00m.

Laminated to thickly bedded mudstone (grey domains) to sandstone (tan domains). 	Graded beds facing down-hole. 	Pervasive sericite +- carbonate alteration. Trace disseminated pyrite. 	Occasional boudinaged quartz-carbonate veins, <4cm wide. 	Contorted and folded beds from ~20-22m. 	22-22.40m: massive quartz-carbonate vein. 	22.52-23.70m: very broken and fragmented rock; possible fault zone.

Olive green to greyish, mixed sedimentary facies with fragments of ultramafic, mafic and quartz-carbonate veins. Sedimentary matrix grades from sandstone to mudstone domiant over 10 m domains (see below).  ~10-30% irregular deformed fragments in a foliated sand-sized matrix. Fragments include: dominantly quartz-carbonate veins with pressure shadows, wispy foliated ultramafic fragments, dark grey-black aphanitic fragments

Pervasive carbonate-sericite-chlorite alteration and weak disseminated pyrite.Gradational lower contact to ultramafic facies.

Brecciated ultramafic; breccia texture defined by white quartz-carbonate infill. Pervasive chlorite-carbonate alteration, gradational to stronger carbonate-quartz alteration at the lower contact. Orange (oxidized) to ~57.5m depth. Trace to no disseminated pyrite.

Albite-quartz-altered aphanitic dykes/boundins and feldspar-phyric felsic dykes. Albitite dykes / boudins have irregular wispy fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic inclusions, or ragged, irregular margins. Felsic dykes from 59.68 to 60.00m, and from 60.50 to 60.80m, are pinkish and have faint feldspar crystals. 	Strong disseminated pyrite in albite-altered aphanitic domains.

Massive green-grey to brown ultramafic with a fine- to medium-grained granular texture; local spinifex texture. 	Irregular and deformed quartz-carbonate vein stockwork. Pervasive carbonate-quartz alteration with very weak fuchsite and very weak sericite-chlorite alteration. 	Fine-grained disseminated pyrite (0.5-1%).

Emerald green wispy banded ultramafic with 40-60% white quartz-carbonate infill. 	Local spinifex texture in UM fragments. 	Pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration. 	Strong (1-2%) disseminated pyrite + chalcopyrite. 	Irregular brown, strongly albite-carbonate- disseminated pyrite boudins at 97.45 to 97.72m.

Apple to emerald green massive ultramafic with irregular wispy albitic dykes/boudins up to 30cm diameter. 	Pervasive fuchsite-sericite-quartz-carbonate alteration of ultramafic. Pervasive albite-quartz alteration of abitites. 10-30% quartz-carbonate stockwork veins – disseminated sulfides concentrated in the vein envelopes. Strong (1-2%) disseminated pyrite + arsenopyrite.

Tan-grey, aphanitic, albite-quartz altered albitite. Pervasive strong to intense albite-quartz +- sericite alteration. Irregular white quartz-carbonate vein network (<5%). Strong (2-3%) disseminated pyrite (very silvery) and possible trace arsenopyrite. Sharp upper and lower contacts are deformed and brecciated.

Apple green fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic with pale tan boudins of albite. 	Albitic boudins compose ~70% of the rock. 	Pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration of ultramafic. Pervasive albite-quartz-muscovite-carbonate altered albitite. Moderate to strong disseminated pyrite.

Brown, carbonate-quartz altered ultramafic. Pervasive sericite-carbonate-quartz-chlorite alteration. 10-50% quartz-carbonate stockwork infill. Albitite boudins or domains up to 25cm wide. Weak disseminated pyrite and possible arsenopyrite (<0.5%).

Mixed – ultramafic facies; variably altered boulders; dominantly brown carbonate altered ultramafic, 1 boulder of talc-chlorite altered ultramafic and 1 run of fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic. 1-2m intervals separated by non-latching core with subtle alteration and textural variations. Each run has 20cm to 1m of lost recovery. Possible stope fill or slabby boulders on the side of a stope.

Tan, massive, homogenous unit with ragged sericite altered feldspar. Pervasive sericite-carbonate-albite alteration. Strong disseminated pyrite (2-3%). 	Irregular thin stockwork of grey quartz-carbonate veins.

Massive fine-grained, granular textured ultramafic. 	Pervasive carbonate-quartz alteration with weak fuchsite and sericite, and trace chlorite. 	5-10% irregular quartz-carbonate vein network. Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).
Mixed – ultramafic facies; variably altered boulders; dominantly brown carbonate-sericite ultramafic and fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic. Fragments < 15cm.

Polymictic breccia with variably altered  angular ultramafic and albitic fragments, < 3cm, in a sand-sized matrix and ~10-15% quartz cement. Pervasive quartz-carbonate fuchsite alteration +- albite +- sericite +- chlorite. 	Wispy lenses of disseminated pyrite (very silivery-arsenian pyrite); possible fragments. Fine disseminated pyrite (0.5%).

Massive ultramafic with pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration. Locally “flooded” with quartz-carbonate/silicified zones. QC cement discrete vein breccias (5-30cm wide domains). 	Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).

Poor recovery, possible fill material; 1m to 50 cm core loss on each run through this interval. Domains of ultramafic, up to 2 m, separated by zones of angular rubble. 	Massive fine- to coarse-grained granular ultramafic. 	Moderate pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration. ~10% QC vein stockwork, dominantly white but locally veins are grey “smokey”. Silicified fault breccia from 178.39 to 179.2m. Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).

Not confident in the lithology - may be mixed or obscured by intense foliation	.Poor recovery to 185.00m. Dark grey-black banded unit with strong pervasive quartz-graphite alteration. 	Strong foliation, banded alteration, and sheared and faulted quartz-carbonate veins. Bottom contact, from 190.6 to 191.0 is a gravelly fault that marks an abrupt change in foliation intensity (strong up-hole and moderate to weak down-hole). Weak bands of fuchsite from 179.17 to 186.0m. Graphitic fracture surfaces and irregular foliated domains. Strong disseminated pyrite (2-5%), trace arsenopyrite.

Homogeneous, massive dark grey unit, fine-grained unit. 	Planar grey quartz-carb veins ~1-2 cm, ~ 1 per m. 	Pervasive albitic-carbonate alteration; very weak reaction to HCl. 	Weak disseminated pyrite (<0.5%).

Monomictic mafic breccia with pale pink varioles and zones of coalesced varioles, banded dark green-black and grey. 	Patchy foliation parallel albite-carbonate alteration, moderate reaction to HCl. 	Locally strong disseminated pyrite and arsenopyrite; mineraliation particularly enriched after 217.12m.

Graphitic interbed from 233.03 to 233.30m separating albite-quartz-altered mafic facies. Graphitic fault breccia from 233.67 to 234.20m with a large white quartz-carbonate vein. Strong disseminated pyrite and trace arsenopyrite.

Dark grey unit of strongly silificed and pyrite mineralized breccia of dominantly mafic composition. Other fragments include:quartz-vein fragments and black mudstone fragments. BX texture interpreted to be the result of a tectonic or hydorthermal overprint. Intense pervasive quartz-albite alteration. Very strong disseminated pyrite and arsenopyrite.

Grey, strongly foliated ultramafic, possible mixed zone of mafic protolith (Cr values on pXRF vary from 200 to 800 ppm throughout). 	Strong to intense quartz-carbonate alteration, weak or diffuse fuchsite alteration, weak patchy sericite-chlroite alteration. Irregular fragmented smokey quartz veins. Patchy moderate to strong disseminated pyrite.
Grey, strongly foliated and banded ultramafic. 	Bands of grey-white quartz-carbonate and muscovite-chlorite altered ultramafic. Patchy weak to moderate pyrite.
Banded carbonate (+calcite)-chlorite altered ultramafic (strong reaction to HCl). Very strongly foliated, 40degTCA. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Bedded sandstone to mudstone; laminated to thickly bedded. Thickly bedded sandstone beds up to 1m thick from 6.45 to 11.35m, thereafter mudstone dominant. 	Planar to contorted and folded beds; normally graded – facing downhole. 	Pervasive sericite-muscovite-chlorite alteration. Irregular brecciated quatz-carbonate veins; <2cm thick. 	25.98-26.87m: broken core with a 15cm wide chunky quartz-carboante vein; possible fault zone. 	Gradational lower contact.

Olive greenish-grey unit with pervasive carbonate-sericite-chlorite alteration. Deformed and foliated mixed ultramafic and clastic facies with fragments and boudins of quartz-carbonate veins and lithics. Domains of sandstone dominant (32.30-38.72m), mudstone dominant (38.72-50.20m), and ultramafic dominant (50.20-57.34m). 	Gradational lower contact to ultramafic facies.
Brecciated ultramafic; breccia texture defined by white quartz-carbonate infill. Pervasive chlorite-carbonate alteration. Trace to no disseminated pyrite.
Albite-quartz-sericite altered unit. 	Irregular wispy fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic inclusions, or ragged, irregular margins. Moderate to strong disseminated pyrite.

Brown to greenish, massive ultramafic with a fine- to medium-grained granular texture. 	Fine-grained to aphanitic dykes/boudins/non-veined intervals from 81.35 – 81.82m and 82.53 – 82.76m; possible dykes (mafic or ultramafic?). Irregular and deformed quartz-carbonate vein stockwork. Trace to no disseminated pyrite. 	Gradational lower alteration and vein intensity contact.

Emerald green wispy banded ultramafic with 40-60% white quartz-carbonate infill. 	Local spinifex texture in UM fragments. 	Pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration. Strong (1-2%) disseminated pyrite.

Albitite unit with irregular ultramafic inclusions.	Pale greyish-brown, fine-grained unit with gradational brecciated margins to quartz-carbonate-chlorite altered ultramafic. 	Pervasive albite-carbonate-sericite altered. Gradational upper contact with massive to granular ultramafic facies with weak fuchsite alteration. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Emerald green wispy banded ultramafic with ~40% white quartz-carbonate infill. Strong disseminated pyrite-arsenopyrite and tetrahedrite mineralization. Quartz vein at 122.52m has coarse tetrathedrite,0.5cm wide blebby aggregate. Irregular ragged albitite fragments locally.

Apple green massive ultramafic gradational to strongly QC banded ultramafic upper and lower contacts. Pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate alteration with weak to moderate patchy sericite. 	Strong pyrite mineralization.
Emerald green wispy banded ultramafic with ~ 40% white quartz-carbonate infill. 	Strong pyrite-tetrahedrite mineralization. 	Tetrahedrite clusters, up to 0.5cm, in white quartz veins.

Grey brown, gradational upper alteration contact with weak fuchsite grading into sericite-chlorite dominant. 	Strongly foliated with S1 foliation overprinted by S2 foliation. 	Pervasive quartz-carbonate alteration with sericite-chlorite alteration. White quartz carbonate bands are highly folded. Moderate disseminated pyrite.
Dark blue black chlorite-carbonate altered ultramafic. Quartz-carbonate banded to massive. Strongly foliated with S1 foliation overprinted by S2 foliation. Moderate to strong disseminated pyrite.

Pale pink,very siliceous dyke (unclear whether this is a dyke or a vein); fine dusting of hematite. Faint feldspar phenocrysts , < 1mm. White quartz-carbonate breccia infill locally. Very folded and contorted upper contact (small dyke at 154m).

Dark blue black chlorite-carbonate altered ultramafic; possible trace talc. Ultramafic locally has a well-developed breccia texture with angular to wispy fragments and a white quartz-carbonate altered matrix and cement. 	Also massive domains within the ultramafic. Moderate disseminated pyrite and chalcopyrite.

Recovery on runs ranges from 1.37 to 1.81m (loss of 1.20 to 1.60m per 3 m run). Ultramafic boulders up to 1.5m with variable alteration (fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered, sericite-quartz-carbonate altered, chlorite-quartz-carbonate altered) and quartz-carbonate altered to banded. Polylithic gravel, subround to subangular. Sampled boulders on alteration breaks and separately polylithic rubble.

Possible boulders; 50cm of void between 195 and 192.00m. 	Grey-green pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered massive ultramafic. 	Irregular grey-white quartz-carbonate stockwork. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Recover ranges from 1.56 to 2.21m (loss of 0.80 to 1.50m per 3 m run). 	Polylithic angular to subround gravel and boulders up to 0.60cm. Dominantly fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered ultramafic but some dark mafic fragments and quartz vein fragments as well.

Grey-green pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered massive ultramafic with a fine to medium-grained granular texture. 	Irregular stockwork of white-grey quartz-carbonate veins. Weak disseminated pyrite.

Boulders up to 1m wide with zones of poor recovery. Boulders dominantly  ultramafic with variable alteration: fuchsite-quartz-carbonate, sericite-quartz-carbonate, chlorite-quartz carbonate, and variable abundance of quartz-carbonate veining and disseminated sulfides.

Grey-green pervasive fuchsite-quartz-carbonate altered. Massive ultramafic with a fine- to medium-grained granular texture. 	Irregular stockwork of white quartz-carbonate veins. 	Weak disseminated pyrite.

Boulders up to 1.5m wide with recovery ranging from  2.47 to 0.97m (0.50 to 2.0 m of loss per 3 m run). Dominantly ultramafic with variable alteration and textures. Polylithic angular rubble; ultramafic, mafic and vein fragments.

Dark grey, greenish, faintly foliated or bedded unit with minor carbonaceous laminae. Pervasive quartz-carbonate alteration with very weak or subtle fuchsite-chlorite alteration. Grey quartz stockwork veins throughout. Weak disseminated pyrite and blebby chalcopyrite. Tennantite in the centre of cockade quartz-carbonate veins (steel grey sulfide with a grey streak).
Boulders, up to 20 cm wide of emerald green fuchsite-quartz-carb altered ultramafic; core redrilled over this interval

Dark grey, greenish banded and foliated unit with thin graphitic or carbonaceous laminae; possible graded bedding may indicate up-hole younging. Grey to white thin and irregular quartz-carbonate vein stockwork; grey quartz-dominant veins locally have an insitu breccia texture. Dissemianted pyrite, chalcopyrite and tennantite.

Dark grey with a subtle purplish hue unit with bedded or mixed dark graphitic or carbonaceous interbeds. Perlite texture developed in monomictic breccia domains. Pervasive quartz-albite-carbonate alteration. Strong disseminated pyrite + trace arsenopyrite. 	Interval is fractured and friable with a gritty coating on fracture surfaces.	Gradational lower contact to massive mafic unit.

Grey with a subtle purplish hue – massive homogeneous mafic unit. 	Upper contact is irregular and contains inclusions or beds of black graphitic or carbonaceous sediment infill. Subtle brecciation and minor black graphitic mudstone infill. Pervasive quartz-albite-carbonate alteration. Weak disseminated pyrite-chalcopyrite.

Dark grey purplish monomictic mafic breccia. Well developed perlite texture; and curviplanar perlitic fragments, < 2cm throughout. Weakly banded with black graphitic mudstone-sandstone interbeds. 	Strong pervasive albite-quartz-carbonate alteration. 	Strong disseminated pyrite and locally intense quartz-vein stockwork; up to 15% pyrite, minor trace arsenopyrite.

Black graphitic mudstone, 50 cm wide interbed at the top and bottom contact  of this interval. Large colloform and cockade white quartz-carbonate veins, 15 cm wide. Strongly silicified and mineralized mafic (strong to intense pervasive albite-quartz “flooded” mafic). Graphitic fault gouge at 306.27 (10cm wide, ~90deg TCA). Strong to intense disseminated pyrite with lesser chalcopyrite with trace arsenopyrite.

Grey with a subtle purplish hue. Mafic- massive to monomictic breccia; weak graphitic mudstone infill. Pervasive quartz-albite alteration with graphitic coating on fracture surfaces. Very fine-grained, weak to moderate disseminated pyrite.

Olive green massive ultramafic. Pervasive sericite-quartz-carbonate alteration. Minor irregular white quartz-carbonate veins. Weak to trace disseminated pyrite. Possible fault at lower contact; 40cm wide zone of angular rubble and sand coating fracture surfaces.

Dark grey banded ultramafic unit; possibly mixed  with sandstone or mudstone facies (unsure of this lithology pick). 	Pervasive quartz-carbonate-chlorite alteration with weak calcite. 	Bands of smokey quartz-carbonate veins. Moderate to strong disseminated pyrite (euhedral and subhedral brassy phases).
